This is the official driver from Realtek and can be loaded instead of
the FreeBSD driver built into the GENERIC kernel if you experience
issues with it (eg. watchdog timeouts), or your card is not supported.

Please note this driver requires a system reboot to activate.

For OPNsense tuning, keep the plugin defaults unchanged and add optional
loader tunables in System: Settings: Tunables only when troubleshooting
or benchmarking specific hardware:

- hw.re.intr_filter=1 can reduce interrupt overhead on MSI/MSI-X capable
  hardware.
- hw.re.msi_disable=1 or hw.re.msix_disable=1 can improve stability on
  systems that show interrupt-related issues.
- dev.re.N.int_rx_mod controls receive interrupt moderation. Lower values
  reduce latency, higher values can reduce CPU overhead.

These tunables are hardware-dependent and should not be enabled globally
without verification.

